  "text": "Micromass cultures from chicken limb buds were prepared as described previously. [CITATION_1] Infection was performed with 1 ml of replication competent avian sarcoma (RCAS) viral supernatants containing the cds encoding WT-chicken Bmpr1b (WT-chBmpr1b) or R486W-chBmpr1b as described previously. [CITATION_2] Additional in vitro mutagenesis was performed to introduce the mutation R486Q into the WT-chBmpr1b using the Quick Change site-directed Mutagenesis kit (Stratagene, La Jolla, CA, USA). Culture medium (DMEM-F12, 2% chicken serum, 4 mM L-glutamine, 1000 U/ml penicillin and 100 mg/ml streptomycin) was replaced every 2 days. For each condition, four replicates were performed in parallel. Micromass cultures were fixed and stained with Alcian blue at days 5, 6 and 7. After 10 and 12 days in culture, micromass cultures were fixed and detection of ALP activity was achieved by incubation with NBT-BCIP. Novel R486Q mutation in BMPR1B K Lehmann et al Quantification of Alcian blue and ALP staining were achieved by histomorphometric analyses using the AxioVision software tool AutMess (Zeiss, Carl Zeiss MicroImaging GmbH, Göttingen).",
